<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Beddington Heights</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">A typical suburban neighborhood in North Calgary, Beddington Heights is bound by the 14th Street W on the west, the Beddington Boulevard on the south, the Beddington Trail on the east and the Berkshire Boulevard on the north.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Originally developed as a Canadian Pacific Railway Station, the Beddington Heights real estate was established in 1979 and offers an eclectic assortment of dwellings ranging from duplexes to townhomes and detached units.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">A townhome in the area could typically be purchased for around $400,000 or more.</p>
        </div>
